<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1440,1232,1288]" lastBlockId="14.[192,1440,1504,1657]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,1232,1256]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is most easily recognized by the presence of two strongly erect pubescent tufts on each elytron (
<figureCitation box="[405,529,1264,1288]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="14.[192,275,1367,1389]" captionTargetBox="[215,1440,224,1336]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1440,213,1362]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 7. Duocristala viridifrons Lingafelter, new genus, new species. a) Anterior view, holotype male. b) Head, paratype male. c) Pronotum, paratype male. d) Lateral view, holotype male. e) Dorsal elytron, paratype male. f) Closeup of medial elytral tuft, holotype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3703017/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 7a, d</figureCitation>
): one at the centro-basal position and one medially (
<figureCitation box="[1195,1344,1264,1288]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="14.[192,275,1367,1389]" captionTargetBox="[215,1440,224,1336]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1440,213,1362]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 7. Duocristala viridifrons Lingafelter, new genus, new species. a) Anterior view, holotype male. b) Head, paratype male. c) Pronotum, paratype male. d) Lateral view, holotype male. e) Dorsal elytron, paratype male. f) Closeup of medial elytral tuft, holotype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3703017/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 7d, e, f</figureCitation>
). Other characters include the strongly clavate femora (
<figureCitation box="[781,899,1504,1529]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="16.[192,275,1064,1086]" captionTargetBox="[334,1297,265,1024]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[301,1330,235,1032]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 8. Duocristala viridifrons Lingafelter, new species. a) Dorsal, holotype male. b) Ventral, holotype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703019" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3703019/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8a, b</figureCitation>
), medially swollen antennal scape (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1425,1504,1529]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="16.[192,275,1064,1086]" captionTargetBox="[334,1297,265,1024]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[301,1330,235,1032]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 8. Duocristala viridifrons Lingafelter, new species. a) Dorsal, holotype male. b) Ventral, holotype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703019" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3703019/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8a</figureCitation>
), long interocular seta on frons at edge of lower eye lobe (
<figureCitation box="[892,980,1536,1560]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="14.[192,275,1367,1389]" captionTargetBox="[215,1440,224,1336]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1440,213,1362]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 7. Duocristala viridifrons Lingafelter, new genus, new species. a) Anterior view, holotype male. b) Head, paratype male. c) Pronotum, paratype male. d) Lateral view, holotype male. e) Dorsal elytron, paratype male. f) Closeup of medial elytral tuft, holotype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3703017/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 7b</figureCitation>
), broad pronotum with strong, broad lateral tubercles and large, separate punctures (
<figureCitation box="[792,878,1568,1593]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="14.[192,275,1367,1389]" captionTargetBox="[215,1440,224,1336]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1440,213,1362]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 7. Duocristala viridifrons Lingafelter, new genus, new species. a) Anterior view, holotype male. b) Head, paratype male. c) Pronotum, paratype male. d) Lateral view, holotype male. e) Dorsal elytron, paratype male. f) Closeup of medial elytral tuft, holotype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3703017/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 7c</figureCitation>
), elytra without erect hairs (except for tufts), without a lateral carina, and with rounded apices (
<figureCitation box="[818,904,1600,1625]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="14.[192,275,1367,1389]" captionTargetBox="[215,1440,224,1336]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1440,213,1362]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 7. Duocristala viridifrons Lingafelter, new genus, new species. a) Anterior view, holotype male. b) Head, paratype male. c) Pronotum, paratype male. d) Lateral view, holotype male. e) Dorsal elytron, paratype male. f) Closeup of medial elytral tuft, holotype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3703017/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 7e</figureCitation>
). Justification for proposing this new genus is presented in the Remarks, along with comparison to other genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[1060,1235,1632,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Acanthocinini">Acanthocinini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
